l --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
The first thing you need is a nice AOE spell. Circle of force is quite nice, albeit research-only. Get a nice aoe-snare up too, (bonds of force) and away you go!<br>
This is best done around 39 - as Stormyn can well attest, it's (to use his own words) &quot;insane experience&quot;. Head to the Oasis of Marr. Nice place, mind the big named sand giant (I'll get my revenge yet, Cazel!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and head south, to the southern part of the oasis and Spec isle.<br>
 Specters. Right. Nice things. Your best friends for the next few levels, if you treat them right. Cast an O'Keil's Levity, get those journeyman's boots on (or, for the cheaper ones out there, chug one of Kajer's handy-dandy 10 dose Blood of the Wolf) for a little running speed, and away you go!<br>
  Fly towards the isle. Use a little level one nuke (shock of frost* works very well) to pull your first specter, then circle round, getting three others. Run rings around them in the southern part of teh desert, so as to stay near enough to a zone as to be safe... And, once they're all packed, either snare them, or start with the Circle of Force. It all depends on how much you plan on running... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
  With a Kei, you can also octo-kite them; no snaring if you have eight spec's on your tail, since bonds of force only hits four targets; but the rewards are greater. Plus, it's more fun! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
   This is just one of the places you can do this in. Above 44, I'd recommend you get a group; once you hit 51, though, it's off to Cobalt Scar to do the same thing to the Wyverns there!<br>
<br>
   *Yes, shock of frost. Why? Because by the time you've pulled all the specters, you'll need your mana - and most of the damage from a nastier spell will have been healed anyway. And you want those specs to fall all at the same time, believe me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
